{"parentUuid":"9bdf5c97-e689-454c-bd2b-72d02ffcc218","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"9f8d213a-3399-44ab-b77b-4ed0f6b6d4f5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a8c763669fac8abaf","slug":"velvety-tinkering-coral","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nkuz25m7wPvtGzitCTcZ8B","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 52\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/52](https://www.erdosproblems.com/52)\n    23→\n    24→The Erdős–Szemerédi sum-product conjecture [ErSz83]: for every $\\varepsilon > 0$ there exists\n    25→$c > 0$ such that $\\max(|A+A|, |A \\cdot A|) \\geq c \\cdot |A|^{2-\\varepsilon}$ for every finite\n    26→set $A$ of integers. The best known bound is due to Bloom [Bl25].\n    27→\n    28→[ErSz83] Erdős, P. and Szemerédi, E., *On sums and products of integers*.\n    29→Studies in pure mathematics, Birkhäuser, Basel (1983), 213–218.\n    30→\n    31→[Bl25] Bloom, T., *New bounds on the sum-product problem* (2025).\n    32→-/\n    33→\n    34→open Finset Real\n    35→\n    36→open scoped Pointwise\n    37→\n    38→namespace Erdos52\n    39→\n    40→/--\n    41→**Erdős Problem #52** (The Sum-Product Conjecture):\n    42→\n    43→For every $\\epsilon > 0$, there exists $c > 0$ such that for every finite set\n    44→$A$ of integers with $|A| \\geq 2$,\n    45→$$\\max(|A + A|, |A \\cdot A|) \\geq c \\cdot |A|^{2 - \\epsilon}.$$\n    46→\n    47→A problem of Erdős and Szemerédi [ErSz83]. The current best lower bound is\n    48→$\\max(|A+A|, |AA|) \\gg |A|^{1270/951 - o(1)}$ due to Bloom [Bl25].\n    49→-/\n    50→@[category research open, AMS 5 11]\n    51→theorem erdos_52 :\n    52→    ∀ ε : ℝ, ε > 0 →\n    53→    ∃ c : ℝ, c > 0 ∧\n    54→    ∀ A : Finset ℤ, (A.card : ℝ) ≥ 2 →\n    55→    max ((A + A).card : ℝ) ((A * A).card : ℝ) ≥ c * (A.card : ℝ) ^ (2 - ε) := by\n    56→  sorry\n    57→\n    58→end Erdos52\n    59→"}]},"uuid":"b521c640-64ed-4645-9506-84a3de7b7a19","timestamp":"2026-03-09T20:47:24.708Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9bdf5c97-e689-454c-bd2b-72d02ffcc218"}
{"parentUuid":"b521c640-64ed-4645-9506-84a3de7b7a19","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"9f8d213a-3399-44ab-b77b-4ed0f6b6d4f5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a8c763669fac8abaf","slug":"velvety-tinkering-coral","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01ASP7FYc9VvLuFZstaPL26z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I found the file containing Erdos Problem 52 formalization.\n\n**File Path:** `/home/ryan/formal-conjectures/FormalConjectures/ErdosProblems/52.lean`\n\n**Contents:**\n\nThe file contains the formalization of Erdős Problem 52, known as the Erdős–Szemerédi sum-product conjecture. The main theorem is:\n\n```lean\n@[category research open, AMS 5 11]\ntheorem erdos_52 :\n    ∀ ε : ℝ, ε > 0 →\n    ∃ c : ℝ, c > 0 ∧\n    ∀ A : Finset ℤ, (A.card : ℝ) ≥ 2 →\n    max ((A + A).card : ℝ) ((A * A).card : ℝ) ≥ c * (A.card : ℝ) ^ (2 - ε) := by\n  sorry\n```\n\nThe theorem formalizes the conjecture: For every ε > 0, there exists c > 0 such that for every finite set A of integers with |A| ≥ 2, max(|A + A|, |A · A|) ≥ c · |A|^(2 - ε). The current best known lower bound is |A|^(1270/951 - o(1)) due to Bloom (2025)."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1285,"cache_read_input_tokens":12838,"output_tokens":360,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1285},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CYtANdJiAx8VX8Zfxhgm9","type":"assistant","uuid":"6664eb4a-f1fd-4943-a2aa-c65362653154","timestamp":"2026-03-09T20:47:27.518Z"}
